        "id": 1046320
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-05T08:24:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "you have good point here.\nAs David mentioned earlier, it might be better not to tinker with SIGALARM but to fix the socket_connect() function instead. Since there is no clear way to fix socket_connect() yet, putting BEGIN_/END_NOSIGALRM here at least won\u0027t cause any unexpected negative effects since it is at quit early stage.\nwhat do you think ?\n\nDavid, do you have any suggestions on how to fix socket_connect properly?",
      "parentUuid": "929c86d9_d3cd0cb1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 364,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 364,
        "endChar": 65
      },
