    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "929c86d9_b0a2f6fc",
        "filename": "android/qemu-setup.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 367,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-04T21:17:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You should definitely *not* exit here. The cufrent behaviour is intentional, and is to notify any existing ADB server that a new emulator instance has started (so that it will get listed through \"adb devices\").\n\nIf an ADB server is not running, the emulator should just start, and we definitely want to keep things running this way. If you have a problem for CI, you should modify your scripts to always ensure that the ADB server runs before launching the emulators instead.",
      "parentUuid": "52a68e28_8e0b5ba6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 367,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 367,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "e63bf95afe5b5e619700d408cc59a0953f15591d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "52a68e28_6e98afbf",
        "filename": "android/qemu-setup.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 367,
      "author": {
        "id": 1068239
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-04T21:27:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I\u0027ll rollback this. But it was useful to me to have emulators exiting during CI (because, it makes me able to validate that this connect EINTR/EISCONN does not occurs anymore.\nLast word, I think it could happened somewhere else, on other syscalls, as it happens for fork. Maybe some other issues can be related to SIGARLM interruptions.",
      "parentUuid": "929c86d9_b0a2f6fc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 367,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 367,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "e63bf95afe5b5e619700d408cc59a0953f15591d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "12da56a9_cc69dff9",
        "filename": "android/sockets.c",
