        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-04T21:17:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like the problem is really that socket_connect() will retry on EINTR, while the socket is already connected. It might be better to fix socket_connect() in this case.",
      "revId": "e63bf95afe5b5e619700d408cc59a0953f15591d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d742704b_effaa1c3",
        "filename": "android/sockets.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 1270,
      "author": {
        "id": 1046320
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-05T07:14:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "strangely, when this happens (EISCONN), sometimes the socket is able to write and adb can detect the emulator; some times the socket cannot write  (errno ENOTCONN) and adb cannot detect emulator.",
      "parentUuid": "12da56a9_cc69dff9",
      "revId": "e63bf95afe5b5e619700d408cc59a0953f15591d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
